* Iron Raptor almost whimpered when Element let go of her, dropping like a 
rock to the ground.
But, by some stroke of luck, she hit the ground with her front arms and was 
kinda standing on her hands for a few moments before her back legs dropped 
to ground and she quickly transformed back into robot mode.
Her armor was repaired, even the gash in her side was gone.
Iron Raptor stood up and brushed herself off a bit, clearing her throat but 
stopping short when she saw Element smack Prowl.
She cringed at the sound, turning her stomack.
< Eww...>
She cleared her throat again.*

" You really didn't have to do that, you know."

* Iron Raptor looked way up at Element, shading her eyes from what little 
sun peeked through the thinning ash.*

" Um...I'm Iron Raptor, Maximal Commander. Hmm...who are you?"

* Iris walked up beside Iron Raptor, sighing and shaking her head at the 
sight of Prowl's limp body.
< How praductable.> she thought as she walked up to the base of Element.*

" You can put him down now. No more trouble will come from that man."

* Iris turned back to Iron Raptor, glaring at her from under her helm.*

" Shouldn't you be concerned about that meeting Angel Prime disappeared to? 
He said that you should be there."

* Iron Raptor glanced at Iris, her hair slightly in her eyes and falling 
down her shoulders.*
< There's something a little bigger that needs my attention.>
< And what's that, this thing?> Iris asked, gesturing towards Element.
< No, > Iron answered. < Something that the entire Maximals crew can take 
part in...but I need Prowl awake first.>
